# Algerian Forest Fires Prediction using Machine Learning

## Project Overview
This project performs Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), data preprocessing, feature engineering, and machine learning modeling on the Algerian Forest Fires dataset. The objective is to understand the relationship between meteorological conditions and fire weather indices and to build predictive models that can help assess forest fire risk.

The project follows a structured and realistic data science workflow, focusing on data quality, interpretability, and model robustness.

---

## Dataset Description
The dataset contains observations related to forest fire occurrences in two regions of Algeria:
- Bejaia Region (Northeast Algeria)
- Sidi Bel-Abbes Region (Northwest Algeria)

The data includes meteorological variables and Fire Weather Index (FWI) components recorded during the fire season.

---

## Features

### Meteorological Variables
- Temperature (°C)
- Relative Humidity (%)
- Wind Speed (km/h)
- Rain (mm)

### Fire Weather Index Components
- FFMC (Fine Fuel Moisture Code)
- DMC (Duff Moisture Code)
- DC (Drought Code)
- ISI (Initial Spread Index)
- BUI (Buildup Index)
- FWI (Fire Weather Index)

### Target Variable
- Fire occurrence / fire severity indicator

