---

## Exploratory Data Analysis
The EDA focuses on:
- Understanding feature distributions using histograms
- Identifying skewness and outliers
- Analyzing correlations between fire weather indices
- Comparing patterns across regions
- Detecting data quality issues and inconsistencies

Insights from EDA directly guide feature engineering and model selection.

---

## Data Cleaning and Feature Engineering
Key steps include:
- Handling missing and inconsistent values
- Converting categorical variables into numerical form
- Feature scaling and normalization
- Removing redundant or highly correlated features

These steps improve model stability and performance.

---

## Machine Learning Modeling
The modeling workflow includes:
- Train-test split
- Model training
- Model evaluation
- Error analysis and performance comparison

The focus is on generalization and avoiding data leakage.

---

## Model Evaluation
The following evaluation metrics are used depending on the modeling objective:
- Mean Squared Error (MSE)
- Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)
- R-squared (R²)

---

## Key Observations
- Fire Weather Index components are strongly associated with fire occurrence
- Regional differences influence fire behavior
- Proper preprocessing improves model convergence and reliability

